Manhattan Beach Railroad, now Long Island Railroad, eastward from the Myrtle Ave. Elevated station of the B.M.T. at Myrtle and Gates Aves. This is its right-of-way, and not a street. (for further views of the Manhattan
Beach Railroad see the Borough of Queens).
August 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
